      • getArgumentListNode

        public ArgumentListNode getArgumentListNode()
        The the TreeNode that represents the arguments to the method call. For example:
         methodName(5, "Arg2", 3 * n);
        In the previous statement, the data within the parenthesis are the arguments passed to the method. The ArgumentNode returned by this method would contain a node for each of the arguments passed, in the correct order from left to right.
        Returns:
        The TreeNode that represents the arguments to the method call.

      • isExternal

        public boolean isExternal()
        Get whether or not the method is called externally. A method is external if it begins with an externally imported C file's name. For example:
         import "externalFile.h";
 
 ...
 
 public static void main(String args[])
 {
        // This is the external method call.
        externalFile.cFunctionName();
 }
        In this example, 'externalFile' is the C header file that is imported. 'cFunctionName()' is the name of a function that is contained within the imported header file.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the method is called externally.

      • getObjectReferenceIdentifier

        public java.lang.String getObjectReferenceIdentifier()
        Get the name of the object reference identifier for the given MethodCallNode's method node. Static methods return "__static__ClassName" and non-static methods return "this". The call cannot be that of an external method.
        Returns:
        The name of the object reference identifier.

      • getObjectReferenceValue

        public ValueNode getObjectReferenceValue()
        Get the ValueNode that the method was called with for the given MethodCallNode's method node, if it was not called with a specific object. Static methods return "__static__ClassName" and non-static methods return "this". The call cannot be that of an external method.
        Returns:
        The ValueNode that the method was called with.

      • getCorrespondingParameter

        public ParameterNode getCorrespondingParameter(ValueNode argument)
        Get the ParameterNode that the given argument represents.

        For example: 
         public void run(int a, int b, int c)
 {
        ...
 }
 
 run(432, 1, 5);
        If you were to call getCorrespondingParameter(1) on the method call above, you would receive the b ParameterNode.
        Parameters:
        argument - The argument to get the corresponding parameter from.
        Returns:
        The ParameterNode that represents the given argument.

      • getCorrespondingParameter

        public ParameterNode getCorrespondingParameter(int argIndex)
        Get the ParameterNode that the given index represents. The parameters are ordered from left to right, 0 being the first.

        For example: 
         public void run(int a, int b, int c)
 {
        ...
 }
 
 run(432, 1, 5);
        If you were to call getCorrespondingParameter(2) on the method call above, you would receive the c ParameterNode.
        Parameters:
        argIndex - The index of the argument to get the corresponding parameter from.
        Returns:
        The ParameterNode at the given index.

      • decodeStatement

        public static MethodCallNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                             java.lang.String statement,
                             Location location,
                             boolean require,
                             boolean scope)
        Decode the given statement into a MethodCallNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        To determine whether or not a method is called externally, refer to isExternal() for more details on what an external call looks like.
        Example inputs include:
        • methodName(5, varName, methodThatReturnsAValue(), "arg1")
        • externalFile.cFunctionName()
        • methodName('q', 5 * (2 / 3))
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a MethodCallNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        scope - Whether or not the given statement is the beginning of a scope.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a MethodCallNode.

      • interactWord

        public void interactWord(java.lang.String word,
                int wordNumber,
                Bounds bounds,
                int numWords,
                java.lang.String leftDelimiter,
                java.lang.String rightDelimiter,
                TreeNode.ExtraData extra)
        Description copied from class: TreeNode
        Method that is to be overridden. Whenever the iterateWords(String) method is called, this method will be called with the specific word and the number (order) the word came in the statement.
        Overrides:
        interactWord in class TreeNode
        Parameters:
        word - The word that was found.
        wordNumber - The index of the word on a word-by-word basis.
        bounds - The bounds of the word that was found.
        numWords - The number of words that were parsed.
        leftDelimiter - The text that is between the previous word and the current word.
        rightDelimiter - The text that is between the current word and the next word.
        extra - The extra data that may or may not be needed for the interactWord() methods.
        See Also:
        TreeNode.interactWord(java.lang.String, int, net.fathomsoft.nova.util.Bounds, int, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.TreeNode.ExtraData)
